commit.message:
Fix case when inspect.getsourcefile() returns None (#7)

With Python 2 it would later fail on `with open(filename, 'r') as fp` with:
TypeError: coercing to Unicode: need string or buffer, NoneType found
Switched broken pypip.in badges to shields.io (#5)

Call ast.NodeVisitor.__init__()

It isn't defined in Python 3.4, but it's a good subclassing habit
to do it anyway.
Expand Python versions list in setup script
Add a bunch of shield images to the README
Expand the tests with a more complex case
Test on Python 2.6, 3.2, and 3.3, in addition to 2.7 and 3.4
Try both __code__ and func_code attributes for compatibility
Keep track of functions and function local scope
Make test classes extend from built-in object
Use inspect.getsourcefile() to obtain a file name
